    "game-obj": "Equipment",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This rare and highly addictive drug is rumored to be created by wizards working alongside succubi. Taken in the form of lozenges, this drug can heighten the body's pleasure and pain stimuli as well as increase alertness, energy, and euphoria. Serious side effects that can occur include heart attack, stroke, and sudden vision and hearing loss, but these risks do little to deter users.  \n  \nThe save for addiction to succubus kiss is DC 28, and the addiction has the virulent trait.",
        "level": 7,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Alchemical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 6,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 452,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9fde9d3adae06c502c6263570964463e",
                "text": "Alchemical items are powered by reactions of alchemical reagents. Unless otherwise noted, alchemical items aren\u2019t magical and don\u2019t radiate a magical aura.  \n  \nAlchemical creatures are partially powered by alchemical reactions.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "magical",
                        "alt": "magical",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 644
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Consumable",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 36,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 454,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "07336d377bbfcf8d760f34f32f513526",
                "text": "An item with this trait can be used only once. Unless stated otherwise, it\u2019s destroyed after activation. Consumable items include alchemical items and magical consumables such as scrolls and talismans. A character can Craft consumable items in batches of four.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Drug",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 251",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 251",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 22
                        },
                        "page": 251
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "4f00ad7d0a88ed511610782d69953b8f",
                "text": "An item with this trait is a drug, a poison that conveys short-term benefits in addition to harmful side effects and long-term consequences. Each time a creature uses a given drug it must also attempt a saving throw against addiction to that drug.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "poison",
                        "alt": "poison",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 126
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "addiction",
                        "alt": "addiction",
                        "game-obj": "Diseases",
                        "aonid": 15
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Ingested",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 95,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 248",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 248",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 248,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "c80e26f9fa0dbec243b4a76aca7278df",
                "text": "An ingested poison is activated by applying it to food or drink to be consumed by a living creature, or by placing it directly into a living creature\u2019s mouth. A creature attempts a saving throw against such a poison when it consumes the poison or the food or drink treated with the poison. The onset time of ingested poisons typically ranges anywhere from 1 minute to 1 day",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Poison",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 126,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 459,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "31b1fcebcaa04711c9f0d282aa02bfee",
                "text": "An effect with this trait delivers a poison or deals poison damage. An item with this trait is poisonous and might cause an affliction.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
